@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - usageapi/Query
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Query spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetQuery;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListQueries using filters\nquery_definition.display_name,\nquery_definition.version,\nquery_definition.report_query.tenant_id,\nquery_definition.report_query.granularity (+16\nmore);
:Create the OCI resource via CreateQuery when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteQuery with required via\nGetQuery or ListQueries to DELETED\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetQuery or ListQueries\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateQuery only for mutable fields\nquery_definition;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: usageapi
slug: query
kind: Query
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: query_definition
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_usage_queries filters
query_definition.display_name,
query_definition.version,
query_definition.report_query.tenant_id,
query_definition.report_query.granularity (+16
more)
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The generated runtime reuses an existing query
by listing on the required compartmentId request
scope, then matching the returned
queryDefinition payload on displayName, version,
report inputs, and any populated costAnalysisUI
fields.
The SDK surface does not expose lifecycle states
on Query bodies, so create and update settle
through read-after-write GetQuery confirmation
instead of lifecycle polling; a service-local
wrapper converts that confirmed reread into
settled Active status.
In-place updates are limited to queryDefinition;
compartmentId requires replacement and is
rejected before OCI mutation.
Delete retains the finalizer until GetQuery
confirms the query no longer exists.
end note
@enduml
